reviewBlob: Draft. Slightly hazy golden color, medium white head. Nice aroma of dusty cobwebs and damp earth. Taste is overripe dusty and peppery pineapple, dank edges. Delicious.
Draft at Churchkey. Dark maroon brown color, beige head. Aroma of chocolate and licorice. Taste has huge roast, then the peat and the booze waft over you in a sneaky way. I love it.

beerName: Brouwerij Kees Peated Imperial Russian Stout
reviewBlob: Draft at Churchkey. Very dark brown color, big fluffy beige head with good retention. Aroma of burnt brownies, subtle smoke. Taste has dark chocolate and an edge of peat, not overwhelming. Very tasty.
Draft at Churchkey. Jet black, fluffy beige head. Aroma of burnt licorice, burnt espresso, coffee grounds. Taste is rich earthy cocoa powder and anisette. Very nice.

beerName: Union Craft Rye Baby IPA (Orange Peel & Anise)
reviewBlob: Cask at Churchkey. Hazy deep amber color, see pic please with menu for verification. Aroma of spiced and floral orange. Taste has orange liqueur and bitter chocolate, rye bread. Interesting variation on a theme.
Draft at Churchkey. Hazy very pale yellow color, fluffy white head. Nice lemony aroma with other fruity esters. Taste is very bitter and resiny lemon, almost like a mixer. OK.

beerName: Uinta Crooked Line Birthday Suit: 23rd Anniversary
reviewBlob: Draft. Cloudy golden color, white head. Aroma of dusty berries. Taste is tart and peppery raspberries. Nice.

beerName: Birrificio del Ducato Koji Il Riso
reviewBlob: Draft at Churchkey. Cloudy very pale yellow color, thin white head. Aroma of earthy citrus and straw reminds me of a gose. Taste is sour, almost tart raw white bread and light spice. Really interesting.
Draft at Churchkey. Cloudy pale yellow color, bright white head. Aroma of earthy straw, light herbal lemon. Taste is peppery, dusty, earthy hay and straw. Nice.
Draft at Churchkey. Cloudy golden yellow color, see pic please. Aroma of lemons squashed by sweaty feet. Taste is lightly tart lemondrops. Easy drinking.

Draft at Churchkey. Cloudy reddish pink color, light pink edge head. Nice berry aroma, tons of mixed fruity esters. Taste has citrusy tart berries, subtle vanilla, soft sourness. Very easy drinking. Love it.

Draft at Churchkey. Cloudy yellow color, see pic with menu for verification please. Wiw, you can identify all three fruits clearly in the aroma, nicely synergizing. Taste is softly sour with peach solidly up front and passiony mango not far behind, and maybe some grapefruit and pineapple masquerading. Love the manageable abv, so easy to drink now we just need some summer weather. Delicious.
Bottle. Cloudy golden yellow color, white head. Nice fruity aroma with raw bread dough. Taste is softly sour, herbal, grassy. Decent.
Draft at Als. Hazy to cloudy golden amber color, medium white head. Aroma has floral mixed spice, summer fruit. Taste is herbal fruit. Easy drinking for its abv.
Draft at the source, Hazy deep golden color, medium white head. Aroma of earthy citrus. Taste is earthy lemon. Easy drinking.
Draft at the source, wee hours, courtesy of either Al or Fish, I forget. Murky golden orange color. Aroma of mango on steroids. The most bitter beer Ive ever had. Hard to take despite the fruit.

brewerName: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
reviewBlob: Draft. Cloudy pale yellow color. Aroma of citrus. Taste is much more lemonade than beer.
Draft at Als. Pretty close to black color, big brown head. Aroma of coffee, chocolate, background of strawberry. Taste is fruity coffee, chocolate milk.
Draft at the source. Opaque dark brown color, tan head. Nice aroma of bitter cocoa powder. Taste is rich dark chocolate and espresso. Nice.
Draft at Golden Crust. Clear golden amber color, thick off white head with good retention and solid lacing. Aroma of lightly toasted caramel. Taste is toasted caramel biscuit, light tannins. Decent.

beerName: Pizza Boy Sunny Side Up w Guajillo, chili & cinnamon
reviewBlob: Draft at the source. Dark brown color, tan head with solid lacing. Aroma of peppery coffee grounds. Taste has rich coffee, light spice/cinnamon. Very easy drinking.
Draft at the source. Clear deep amber color, tan head with good retention and lacing. Aroma of earthy haystacks, spiced caramel, rye bread. Taste is rye bread. Delicious.

beerName: Mad Chef Spot Hop 5.0 Citrus Mystic
reviewBlob: Draft at the source. Crystal clear golden color, white head with good retention and solid lacing. Aroma of orange peel, lemon peel. Taste is earthy citrus/orange, dry finish. Very easy drinking.

beerName: Mad Chef Once Upon A Porter
reviewBlob: Draft at the source. Clear maroon color, tan head. Aroma of burnt licorice. Taste has burnt coffee, dark cocoa. Tasty.

beerName: Mad Chef It Takes Brew to Mango
reviewBlob: Draft at the source. Cloudy orange color, white edge head. Aroma of mango and orange. Taste is bittersweet tropical fruit. Nice.
Draft at the source. Hazy pale yellow color, thick white head with good retention and lacing. Aroma of freshly peeled citrus. Taste is bitter lemon, straw, raw bread. Tasty.
Draft at the source. Crystal clear yellow color, see pic please. Aroma of dusty hay and light lemon. Taste is herbal grassy lemon. Decent.
Draft at the source. Clear amber color, white head. Aroma of biscuit dipped in caramel. Taste is peppery caramel, light body.
Draft at the source. Crystal clear bright yellow color, fluffy white head. Aroma of white pepper and dusty straw. Taste is clean, crisp, peppery. Spot on.
Draft at Golden Crust. Opaque brown color, tan head. Aroma has nice spice and fruit on a roast background. Taste is spiced cardamom coffee. Tasty.
Draft at Golden Crust. Opaque dark brown color, tan head. Aroma of burnt licorice, burnt espresso. Taste is rich bitter espresso, slightly sweet at the start. Very tasty.
Draft at Golden Crust. Clear golden yellow color, champage bubles. Aroma of tart apple skins. Taste is tart apples with subtle berries. Balanced. Nice.

Draft at the source. Opaque brown color, thin tan head, see pic please. Aroma of sour chocolate. Taste is sort of a sweet and sour peppermint and chocolate kind of thing. Weird, but in a pleasant enough way.
Draft at the source. Slightly hazy pale yellow, see pic please. Aroma has subtle tannins, light vanilla, apple flesh. Tannins are up front in the flavor, with tart apple peel. Very tasty.
Draft at the source. Crystal clear golden yellow, see pic please. Aroma of light aple skins. Taste has apple flesh, lemon, light tannins, dry finish. Mellow.
Draft at the source. Hazy golden amber color, white head with good retention and solid lacing. Aroma of lightly spiced fruit. Taste is fruity hay and peppery straw. Nice.
Draft at the source. Pretty much black, beige head, see pic please. Aroma of burnt brownies. Taste is pine needles dipped in espresso. Dry finish. Tasty.

beerName: Turkey Hill Donnys Irish Dry Stout
reviewBlob: Draft at the source. Opaque dark brown color, thick tan head with good retention and lacing. Aroma of coffee grounds and cocoa powder. Taste is earthy and dry coffee. Light nody. Decent.
Draft at the source. Clear golden amber color, thick creamy head with good retention and solid lacing. Floral aroma with light spice. Taste is lightly oniony, earthy, decent.

beerName: Turkey Hill New Whirrld Vienna Lager
reviewBlob: Draft at the source. Clear amber color. Caramel aroma. Taste is lightly vinous caramel. OK.

beerName: Turkey Hill St. Abbans Irish Red Ale
reviewBlob: Draft at the source. Clear reddish amber color, tan head. Toasted caramel aroma. Taste is herbal caramel. Decent.
Hazy golden color, see pic with menu for verification. Floral aroma. Taste is floral, herbal delicate, dry. Nice.

Draft at the source. Cloudy orange yellow color, bright white head. Aroma of raw bread dough. Taste is white pepper and light funk. Interesting and tasty variation on a theme. Germans everywhere are panicking.
Draft at the source. Hazy variegated golden amber color, white head. Lightlybtoasted caramel aroma. Taste is buttery butterscotch.

beerName: Marleys Pack Dog Peanut Butter Ale
reviewBlob: Draft at the source. Clear golden amber color, flat. Aroma of nutty caramel. Taste is peanut butter. A bit weird to see a lighter beer with pb, but its pleasant enough.
Draft at the source. Hazy variegated golden amber color, white head. Aroma of lightly soced brown bread. Taste has light spice, slick mouthfeel. OK.
Draft at the source. Clear yellow color, scant head. Herbal aroma. Buttery taste, slick oily mouthfeel.

beerName: Old Forge The Eleven Cascadian Dark Ale
reviewBlob: Draft at the source. Pretty much black color, beige head with good retention and solid lacing. Aroma of pine boughs dipped in coffee. Taste is bitter espresso and pine. Very nice.
Draft at the source. Clear golden color, white head with solid lacing. Aroma of lightly funky fruit. Taste is bittersweet summer fruit. Decent.
Draft at the source. Clear golden color, white head with solid lacing. Lightly fruity aroma. Taste is bitter fruit and pine resin. Tasty.
